{
  "text": "The most serious problems relate to the provision of infrastructure. Apart from the reforms needed in irrigation subsidies and power tariffs to improve the efficient use of existing infrastructure, there is also the need for massive investment in providing transport and power (see [CITATION_1] . The remedies for these planners' headaches exacerbated by population growth are well known.",
